     </xref>
     ). A moderate increase in binding (24 ± 3%) was seen when wild-type VAMP4 was incorporated in place of VAMP4-AA. In the presence of 50 nM Arf1, however, the majority (71 ± 4%) of AP-1 bound to VAMP4 liposomes. Binding to liposomes containing 5 mol% PI(4)P was significant at 47 ± 6%, but showed little dependence on Arf1. The incorporation of PI(4)P into liposomes bearing VAMP4 and Arf1 drove binding essentially to completion at 86 ± 4%, (
     <xref ref-type="fig">
