     </xref>
     ). However, β1
     <sup>
      ΔArf1
     </sup>
     and β1/γ
     <sup>
      ΔArf1
     </sup>
     are completely insensitive to the presence of Arf1 (
     <xref ref-type="fig">
      Fig. 7A, B
     </xref>
     ), consistent with their complete or nearly complete loss of activation by Arf1. In contrast, γ
     <sup>
      Arf1
     </sup>
     behaves like wild-type in both the presence and absence of Arf1 (
     <xref ref-type="fig">
      Fig. 7A, B
     </xref>
     ), consistent with the concept that the γ recruitment site does not function in the activation step.
    </p>
